 -  - paper title: Engineered biological nanofactories trigger quorum sensing response in targeted bacteria
 - abstract: Biological nanofactories selectively bind to bacteria and produce molecules that trigger a quorum sensing response and facilitate the communication with nearby bacteria, offering a way to generate new antimicrobial treatments.
